choices.text:
social networks

Frame from a song from a group called You Tube that ran on the Slovak version of TV talent show Big Brother says "I'm too busy to comment for Slovaks. That's why I live abroad." source: YouTube/screenshot You Tube - 2ne1 na Slovensku

People in Slovakia are obsessed with social networks. That’s why everybody has only 150 friends and not 10,00 recognised real friends.

Young people in society today have forgotten about what they really should spend less idle time on. For example keeping in touch with friends.

On March 12 Facebook was released here in Slovakia. It is such a captivating and worrying phenomenon that many believe people have forgotten what it is to talk to friends personally, either by phone or in reality.

But Filip Jablonský, a university professor and expert in language translation and Slovak grammar tells The Slovak Spectator:

"People use terms that don’t mean what they think they mean. Facebook makes people think that 1,300 friends is greater than 13. But 1,300 are just numbers, and to be able to use this piece of software with any success does not depend on the number of friends at all, but on the correct selection of those friends."
